# MultiMic Studio — mobile app configuration
#
# Copy this file to `.env` (in this `mobile/` folder) to override the backend the
# app talks to. Expo automatically loads `.env` and inlines any EXPO_PUBLIC_*
# variable at build/start time — no extra dependency needed.
#
# If this is unset, the app falls back to the local LAN backend baked into
# src/config.ts (http://192.168.3.19:8000), so local testing works out of the box.
#
# Examples:
#   Local LAN (default — usually leave unset):
#     EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://192.168.3.19:8000
#   Hosted backend (later, once deployed behind HTTPS):
#     EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://api.your-domain.com
#
# No trailing slash needed (it is trimmed automatically).

EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://192.168.3.19:8000
